<subSubSection lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,1949,2010]" lastBlockId="58.[151,1437,151,1760]" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1949,1974]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from most similar known species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[847,997,1949,1974]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madalena">
<emphasis box="[847,997,1949,1974]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">M. madalena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by male cheliceral armature (smaller proximal apophyses; compare 
<figureCitation box="[498,699,1985,2010]" captionStart="FIGURES 215–222" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1595,1617]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1570]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[151,1436,193,1574]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 215–222. Mesabolivar madalena sp. n. (215–218, ZFMK Ar 19071) and M. inmanis sp. n. (219–222, ZFMK Ar 19072). 215–216, 219–220. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 217–218, 221–222. Tips of left procursi, prolateral and dorsal views. Scale lines: 0.5 (215–216, 219–220, all chelicerae at same scale), 0.3 (217–218, 221–222; all procursi at same scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202573/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 215 and 219</figureCitation>
), by distinctive shape of posterior margin of epigynal plate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 223–226" captionStartId="57.[151,264,1180,1202]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,195,1158]" captionTargetId="figure@57.[151,1436,193,1159]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 223–226. Mesabolivar madalena sp. n. (223–224, ZFMK Ar 19071) and M. inmanis sp. n. (225–226, ZFMK Ar 19072). 223, 225. Epigyna, ventral views. 224, 226. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views (arrow points at V-shaped sclerite). Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202575/files/figure.png" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 225</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[208,254,152,176]" captionStart="FIGURES241–252" captionStartId="61.[151,264,1628,1650]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES241–252. Femaleepigyna in ventral views and cleared female genitalia in dorsal views, Mesabolivar togatus group (part2). 241–242.M.bico sp. n. (ZFMK Ar19065).243–244.M.mimoso sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19069).245–246. M.madalenasp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19071). 247–248. M. inmanis sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19072). 249. M. sp. (“sp. 7” in Astrin et al. 2006) (Br03/100- 14b). 250.M.cyaneomaculatus (Keyserling, 1891) (ZFMK Ar 19075). 251–252.M. claricae sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19083)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202579/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">247</figureCitation>
), by epigynal pocket close to posterior epigynal margin, and by internal female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1375,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 223–226" captionStartId="57.[151,264,1180,1202]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,195,1158]" captionTargetId="figure@57.[151,1436,193,1159]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 223–226. Mesabolivar madalena sp. n. (223–224, ZFMK Ar 19071) and M. inmanis sp. n. (225–226, ZFMK Ar 19072). 223, 225. Epigyna, ventral views. 224, 226. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views (arrow points at V-shaped sclerite). Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202575/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 226</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1386,1431,152,176]" captionStart="FIGURES241–252" captionStartId="61.[151,264,1628,1650]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES241–252. Femaleepigyna in ventral views and cleared female genitalia in dorsal views, Mesabolivar togatus group (part2). 241–242.M.bico sp. n. (ZFMK Ar19065).243–244.M.mimoso sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19069).245–246. M.madalenasp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19071). 247–248. M. inmanis sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19072). 249. M. sp. (“sp. 7” in Astrin et al. 2006) (Br03/100- 14b). 250.M.cyaneomaculatus (Keyserling, 1891) (ZFMK Ar 19075). 251–252.M. claricae sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19083)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202579/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">248</figureCitation>
; without V-shaped sclerite; pore-plate outer margins diverging anteriorly). From other similar relatives (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1305,1429,189,212]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimoso">
<emphasis box="[1305,1429,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. mimoso</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[151,386,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneomaculatus">
<emphasis box="[151,386,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. cyaneomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[404,536,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claricae">
<emphasis box="[404,536,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. claricae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by combination of: armature of male chelicerae (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1289,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 215–222" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1595,1617]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1570]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[151,1436,193,1574]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 215–222. Mesabolivar madalena sp. n. (215–218, ZFMK Ar 19071) and M. inmanis sp. n. (219–222, ZFMK Ar 19072). 215–216, 219–220. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 217–218, 221–222. Tips of left procursi, prolateral and dorsal views. Scale lines: 0.5 (215–216, 219–220, all chelicerae at same scale), 0.3 (217–218, 221–222; all procursi at same scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202573/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 219–220</figureCitation>
; presence of distinct proximal apophyses, in contrast to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[628,860,260,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneomaculatus">
<emphasis box="[628,860,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. cyaneomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[913,1042,260,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claricae">
<emphasis box="[913,1042,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. claricae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); procursus tip with long prolateral apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[279,437,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 215–222" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1595,1617]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1570]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[151,1436,193,1574]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 215–222. Mesabolivar madalena sp. n. (215–218, ZFMK Ar 19071) and M. inmanis sp. n. (219–222, ZFMK Ar 19072). 215–216, 219–220. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 217–218, 221–222. Tips of left procursi, prolateral and dorsal views. Scale lines: 0.5 (215–216, 219–220, all chelicerae at same scale), 0.3 (217–218, 221–222; all procursi at same scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202573/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 221–222</figureCitation>
; in contrast to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[605,730,297,320]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimoso">
<emphasis box="[605,730,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. mimoso</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); by absence of epigynal processes (
<figureCitation box="[1146,1248,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 223–226" captionStartId="57.[151,264,1180,1202]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,195,1158]" captionTargetId="figure@57.[151,1436,193,1159]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 223–226. Mesabolivar madalena sp. n. (223–224, ZFMK Ar 19071) and M. inmanis sp. n. (225–226, ZFMK Ar 19072). 223, 225. Epigyna, ventral views. 224, 226. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views (arrow points at V-shaped sclerite). Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202575/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 225</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1260,1305,296,320]" captionStart="FIGURES241–252" captionStartId="61.[151,264,1628,1650]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[151,1436,193,1607]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES241–252. Femaleepigyna in ventral views and cleared female genitalia in dorsal views, Mesabolivar togatus group (part2). 241–242.M.bico sp. n. (ZFMK Ar19065).243–244.M.mimoso sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19069).245–246. M.madalenasp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19071). 247–248. M. inmanis sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19072). 249. M. sp. (“sp. 7” in Astrin et al. 2006) (Br03/100- 14b). 250.M.cyaneomaculatus (Keyserling, 1891) (ZFMK Ar 19075). 251–252.M. claricae sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19083)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202579/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">247</figureCitation>
; in contrast to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[180,411,332,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneomaculatus">
<emphasis box="[180,411,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. cyaneomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[466,595,332,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claricae">
<emphasis box="[466,595,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. claricae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
