<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1437,151,1760]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,367,392]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the large size of this species (Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1121,1210,369,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inmanis">
<emphasis box="[1121,1210,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">inmanis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
= large, frightful); adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
